### Approach
After analyzing the conditions, we observe that they can be simplified to a single condition: the larger absolute value of the two elements must be at most twice the smaller absolute value. This simplification is derived from the following insights:
- The original conditions involving the absolute sum and difference can be rephrased using the absolute values of the elements.
- The second condition is always true because the sum of the absolute values of two numbers is always at least the maximum of their absolute values.
- The first condition simplifies to the requirement that the larger absolute value is at most twice the smaller one.

